===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Uncertain. Various explanations include:
* A man ({{zh-l|*人}}) with a mark ({{zh-l|*乙}}) on his leg to indicate 10 {{w|Cun (unit)|cun (寸)}} above the foot. ([[Wiktionary:About Chinese/references#L|Lin Yiguang, 1920]])
* Differentiation of {{och-l|乇}}, {{och-l|宅}}, or {{och-l|斥}}. ([[Wiktionary:About Chinese/references#H|He Linyi, 1998]], [[Wiktionary:About Chinese/references#C|Ji Xusheng, 2014]])
* {{liushu|p}} of a hand, more specifically the thumb and the middle finger, stretched out to measure the length of 10 {{w|Cun (unit)|cun (寸)}}. (Shirakawa Shizuka, Lawrence J. Howell)

